<subSubSection id="C3796513FFEAFFF6FF44FC43FE8D14DE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFEAFFF6FF44FC43FE8D14DE" blockId="2.[170,794,986,1203]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FF44FC43FEFA139E" bold="true" box="[170,296,986,1011]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Type data:</emphasis>
This 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFEAFFF6FE8AFC43FE31139E" box="[356,483,986,1011]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="variety" variety="was">variety was</taxonomicName>
proposed based on an undetermined number of males collected in 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FD48FC63FF30145E" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">São Paulo state</collectingRegion>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FE6AFB83FE10145E" box="[388,450,1050,1075]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FE25FB83FD4B145E" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[459,665,1050,1075]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref4557" refString="Moure, J. S.; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S.; Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.). Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region, Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. p. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FDF4FB83FD9F145E" box="[538,589,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the existence of a 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FE96FBA3FE0F143E" box="[376,477,1082,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">holotype</typeStatus>
housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5DFFEAFFF6FDB5FBA3FD49143E" box="[603,667,1082,1107]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
but no primary types of this species were found in that collection (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FF5FFBE3FEA914FE" author="Ramos, K. S. &amp; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R." box="[177,379,1146,1171]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="335 - 361" refId="ref4707" refString="Ramos, K. S.; Kawada, R. &amp; Brandao, C. R. 2015. Type specimens of bees (Hymenoptera, Apidae) deposited in the Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 55 (24): 335 - 361. DOI" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ramos 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FEECFBE3FEE914FE" box="[258,315,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
).The current condition and depository are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3796513FFEAFFF6FF44FB43FEB616DE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDC3698FFEAFFF6FF44FB43FEB616DE" blockId="2.[169,796,1242,1715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FF44FB43FEE3149E" bold="true" box="[170,305,1242,1267]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments:</emphasis>
According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FF5EFB63FEA1157E" author="Schrottky, C." box="[176,371,1274,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="309 - 315" refId="ref4866" refString="Schrottky, C. 1902 a. Hymenopteres noveaux de l'Amerique Meridionale. Anales del Museo Nacional de Buenos Aires, 7: 309 - 315." type="journal article" year="1902">Schrottky, 1902a</bibRefCitation>
) the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FE57FB63FE39157E" box="[441,491,1274,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
specimen was deposited in Schrottky’s own collection. Unfortunately, it is very probable that the 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FE98FAA3FE7A153E" box="[374,424,1338,1363]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
specimen is lost or destroyed, as well as a large number of his primary 
<typeStatus id="54D8883AFFEAFFF6FDBDFAC3FD42151E" box="[595,656,1370,1395]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">types</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FD73FAC3FEE015FE" author="Rasmussen, C. &amp; Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B." pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref4765" refString="Rasmussen, C.; Garcete-Barrett, B. F. &amp; Goncalves, R. B. 2009. Curt Schrottky (1874 - 1937): South American entomology at the beginning of the 20 th century (Hymenoptera, Lepidoptera, Diptera). Zootaxa, 2282: 1 - 50." type="journal article" year="2009">
Rasmussen 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FF45FAE3FF3915FE" box="[171,235,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D1BFFEAFFF6FEA6FAE3FE2B15FE" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[328,505,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FEA6FAE3FE2B15FE" box="[328,505,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Centris obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in South America, being recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FDC5FA03FD4B15DE" box="[555,665,1434,1459]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FD48FA03FEC215BE" country="Argentina" name="Corrientes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Corrientes province</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FECBFA23FEB315BE" box="[293,353,1466,1491]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FE18FA23FDEA15BE" box="[502,568,1466,1491]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Ceará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FDABFA23FD0A15BE" box="[581,728,1466,1491]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FD08FA23FCCB15BE" box="[742,793,1466,1491]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Pará</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FF0CFA43FE85159E" box="[226,343,1498,1523]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
states), 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FE2EFA43FDB8159E" box="[448,618,1498,1523]" name="French Guiana" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FD95FA43FD30159E" box="[635,738,1498,1523]" name="Paraguay" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3747608FFEAFFF6FF44FA63FECE167E" box="[170,284,1530,1555]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A7F87AFFEAFFF6FEC7FA63FE65167E" box="[297,439,1530,1555]" country="Venezuela" name="Merida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Mérida state</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FE27FA63FD46167E" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[457,660,1530,1555]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref4557" refString="Moure, J. S.; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S.; Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.). Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region, Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. p. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B917EA8AFFEAFFF6FDF4FA63FD81167E" box="[538,595,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al.,</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Both sexes of this species have a strong variation in the coloration of the pubescence, which led different authors to describe subspecies, varieties or new species based on this character. Photographs of both sexes can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B69FFEAFFF6FD3EF9E3FEB216DE" author="Vivallo, F. &amp; Zanella, F. C. V." pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref5030" refString="Vivallo, F. &amp; Zanella, F. C. V. 2012. A new species of Centris (Paracentris) Cameron, 1903 from northeastern Brazil, with a key for the Centris species of the Caatinga region (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Zootaxa, 3298: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="2012">Vivallo &amp; Zanella (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
